milestones.description: Guy de Alwis and Ratnayake's 33-run partnership is SL's highest for the 9th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 24 between Tony Opatha and de Silva
Hadlee has become the top wicket-taker for NZ in ODIs with 56 wickets, going past Lance Cairns's 55
This is the lowest match aggregate (301) involving teams New Zealand & Sri Lanka in ODIs
de Silva has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (13) for SL, going past Duleep Mendis
